The paper deals with algorithms and mathematical characterizations related to phylogenetic networks, which are structures used in computational biology to represent evolutionary histories of species. The paper's focus on algorithms and mathematical characterizations suggests that it belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also deals with graph theory and computational geometry, which are covered by the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The paper's use of mathematical models and analysis suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories.
